\lim_{x\rightarrow 0^+}x^x
e^{x\ln x}
\frac\infty\infty
x\to 0^+
y=x^x\iff \ln y=x\ln x=\frac{\ln x}{\frac1x}
\lim_{x\to0^+} \ln y=\lim_{x\to0^+}x\ln x=\lim_{x\to0^+}\frac{\ln x}{\frac1x}=\lim_{x\to0^+}\frac{\frac1x}{-\frac1{x^2}}=\lim_{x\to0^+}(-x)=0
f(x) = x \ln x
\lim_{t \to \infty} e^{-t} = 0
\lim_{x \downarrow 0} f(x) = \lim_{t \to \infty} f(e^{-t})= \lim_{t \to \infty} e^{-t} (-t) = - \lim_{t \to \infty} \frac{t}{e^t} = 0
\lim_{x \downarrow 0} x^x = \lim_{x \downarrow 0} e^{f(x)} = 1
\lim_{x\rightarrow 0^+}x^x= e^{\lim_{x\rightarrow 0^+}x\ln x}
e^x
\lim_{x\rightarrow 0^+}x\ln x=\lim_{x\rightarrow 0^+}\frac{\ln x}{\frac{1}{x}}
